eventDetails: An afternoon of self-care and restoration, through Yin Yoga & Sound Healing. Yin Yoga is a passive, quiet practice, where postures go beyond our muscles and target the deep connective tissues through long-held poses. It is a meditative journey deep into the body, a gateway to the many layers of our physical and energetic being. This practice is calming and contemplative. Sound Healing is an ancient holistic practice, that is proven to promote wellbeing. It is a beautiful soothing experience, where the practitioner is brought on a journey of calming vibrational frequencies, helping to clear energy blockages within the body, mind and soul and provide calming effects on the nervous system. No previous experience for this retreat is required, it is suitable for all human beings! Spaces are limited, booking and payment is required. lisa@holistichw.com
locationInfo: Off Lwr. Beechwood Avenue, Ranelagh, Dublin , al
eventName: Afternoon Retreat | Le Chéile

eventDetails: The Twin Hearts Meditation was developed by Master Choa Kok Sui to help flush out negative thoughts and emotions that congest our mind and body every day. It is practised in over 126 countries around the world and the testimonials of personal healing and positive life transformation have been incredible. Meditating on the Twin Hearts enables the body to absorb a tremendous amount of energy which many refer to as Prana, Chi or life’s energy. This has a flushing and cleansing effect, then stimulating and energising effect through the practitioners’ system resulting in better physical, emotional and mental health. For Stress Relief & Wellbeing. Scientifically validated to reduce stress and anxiety, increase memory, focus and positive brain activity. Flush out negativity and achieve peace and stillness in less than 30 minutes. Scientifically validated Impact of Meditation on Twin Hearts * Happier, Calmer and More Peace * Increase Focus * Increase Memory Recall * Increase Gamma Wave Activity Contact: Damien 087 266 8531
eventName: Twin Hearts Meditation in Clonsilla

eventDetails: We're offering Free Trial Classes to anyone interested in joining the Bray Movement School. A school gives us the opportunity to come together as a collective with the dual objective of working on the material and working on ourselves. Through the group we give ourselves a chance to change, transform and most notably, provide a space to awaken and become conscious. A movement practice will provide the platform and broad range of material to contend with. In taking part in a movement school like this I’ll aim to teach material that will help you foster a lifelong movement practice that is independent in its own way and truly unique to you as an individual. We come together as a group to share that unique perspective and elevate our own understanding of movement as part of a community. The school will follow a curriculum based approach in exposing students to what I feel are fundamental practices (listed below) that relate to the field of movement. The teachings will be delivered in an organised, modular and process-based approach in order to present these various systems as a coherent body of knowledge. Website: ronanlewins.ie/movement-school-free-trial

Meet at: 11.00am Tallaght Luas stop Walk: Tallaght to Grand Canal Dock Distance: 20km From Grand Canal Dock there are many buses available and a Dart Station to return to the city centre. There are no leaders, just people who like to share the enjoyment of the outdoors. Please do not RSVP if you shall not be attending this event.

eventDetails: You'll meet your local guide at the meeting point a little before 11AM and show your booking. Then we'll commence a fascinating walking tour through the streets, sights, and sounds of Dublin old and new. You'll get an unrivalled insight to the history and culture that has shaped the capital you see today - warts and all, discover the lesser-known, intriguing oddities of our city, and get unique insider tips for the rest of your stay. Sites and topics covered include: Dublin Castle, Christchurch, Viking & Medieval Dublin, Temple Bar, fables, folklore and mythology, Trinity College, Stephen's Green, risings and rebellions, writers & rogues and so, so much more... please remember, places are limited and you must book your spot via: https://www.generationtours.com/dublin See you soon!

eventDetails: Embark on an exciting journey into the world of electronics with a Monday night watch along the course. Are you eager to explore electronics but unsure where to begin? Whether you’re a hobbyist tinkering with Arduino, Raspberry Pi, or sensors, or someone looking to refresh their electronics skills, this course is tailored just for you. Say goodbye to intimidating math-heavy lectures; our sessions prioritize hands-on learning and practical applications. Led by Instructor Joe Gryniuk from Lake Washington Technical College, our course follows the engaging “Electronics 110” series available on YouTube. While there may be optional labs and coursework, the focus is on providing you with accessible, beginner-friendly content. Join us every second Monday evening at 7 pm for an hour and a half session filled with discovery and learning. And don’t worry, it’s completely free to attend! Plus, we’ve got you covered with ample tools, parts, and equipment to kickstart your learning journey. We are starting things off on Monday 22nd at 7 pm and then every two weeks after that. No need to RSVP—simply show up and dive in! And don’t forget, there’s ample free parking available and complimentary tea/coffee to keep you refreshed. Ready to take the plunge? Let’s embark on this electrifying journey together! If you are looking for something a bit more free form you are always welcome to visit our non-structured Electronics, Microcontroller and IOT Evening every other Monday.
eventName: Exploring Electronics Together

eventDetails: Do you suffer from anorexia, bulimia, obesity, binge eating, or undereating? Are you sick of trying to control your eating? Is your obsession with food taking over your life? Addictive Eaters Anonymous (AEA) is a worldwide Twelve Step fellowship based on Alcoholics Anonymous. AEA members have found recovery from binge eating, anorexia, bulimia, other forms of addictive eating and compulsive exercise. Through working the Twelve Steps of AEA, members find peace of mind and the ability to live a meaningful and productive life. Wherever you are, whatever your problem with food, AEA can help. AEA meeting every Monday evening 7.30pm - 8.30pm in Dublin. There are no fees and everyone is welcome. Please contact us for meeting venue details. Phone: +353 1 554 9725 Email: contact@aeairl.org Website: www.addictiveeatersanonymous.org Please visit our website for weekly online meetings.

eventDetails: View Locations here: https://fitnessbootcamp.ie/ Fitness Bootcamp are an alternative gym offering outdoor classes, hikes and adventures throughout the year. We cater for those who enjoy people, nature and all the outdoors has to offer. Our business was established back in 2010 as an alternative way to keep fit. Our goal was to create exciting group workouts using outdoor facilities as much as possible and doing so in an environmentally friendly and sustainable manner. Since then we have grown into a multi-dimensional fitness business and we cater for all aspects of outdoor group training, team building, functional corporate workouts and everything in between, whilst still maintaining our core values of combining fitness and nature in an eco friendly way. We put a huge emphasis on the social aspect of our classes so that individuals find it easy to make new friends and we like to organise group outings for members. We like to think our classes are for everybody and you don't need to have any previous fitness experience to enjoy our workouts. When you come to our classes we want you to feel welcome, enjoy your workouts and in time make some friends living in your area.

eventDetails: You'll meet your local guide at the meeting point a little before 11AM and show your booking. Then we'll commence a fascinating walking tour through the streets, sights, and sounds of Dublin old and new. You'll get an unrivalled insight to the history and culture that has shaped the capital you see today - warts and all, discover the lesser-known, intriguing oddities of our city, and get unique insider tips for the rest of your stay. Sites and topics covered include: Dublin Castle, Christchurch, Viking & Medieval Dublin, Temple Bar, fables, folklore and mythology, Trinity College, Stephen's Green, risings and rebellions, writers & rogues and so, so much more... please remember, places are limited and you must book your spot via: https://www.generationtours.com/dublin See you soon!
eventName: Dublin Free Tour - essentials & oddities

eventDetails: A leisurley walk along the River Dodder. Starting in Tallaght and finishing at Grand Canal Dock. The majority of the walk is off the road and passes through Sean Walsh Park, Dodder River Bank Park, Bushy Park and Herbert Park. Meet at: 11.00am Tallaght Luas stop Walk: Tallaght to Grand Canal Dock Distance: 20km From Grand Canal Dock there are many buses available and a Dart Station to return to the city centre. There are no leaders, just people who like to share the enjoyment of the outdoors. Please do not RSVP if you shall not be attending this event.
eventName: Dodder Walk (From Tallaght to  Grand Canal Dock)
